						<!-- body text -->

						<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><ul id="filetoc"><li><a href="#file">File</a></li>
<li><a href="#filehistory">File history</a></li>
<li><a href="#filelinks">File usage</a></li></ul><div class="fullImageLink" id="file"><a href="/embryology/images/5/5c/Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg"><img alt="File:Single human spermatozoa.jpg" src="/embryology/images/thumb/5/5c/Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg/769px-Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg?20100922005151" decoding="async" width="769" height="600" srcset="/embryology/images/5/5c/Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg?20100922005151 1.5x" data-file-width="1000" data-file-height="780" /></a><div class="mw-filepage-resolutioninfo">Size of this preview: <a href="/embryology/images/thumb/5/5c/Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg/769px-Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg" class="mw-thumbnail-link">769 × 600 pixels</a>. <span class="mw-filepage-other-resolutions">Other resolution: <a href="/embryology/images/5/5c/Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg" class="mw-thumbnail-link">1,000 × 780 pixels</a>.</span></div></div>
<div class="fullMedia"><p><a href="/embryology/images/5/5c/Single_human_spermatozoa.jpg" class="internal" title="Single human spermatozoa.jpg">Original file</a> &#8206;<span class="fileInfo">(1,000 × 780 pixels, file size: 53 KB, MIME type: <span class="mime-type">image/jpeg</span>)</span>
</p></div><div id="mw-imagepage-content" lang="en-GB" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Single_Human_Spermatozoa_Morphology">Single Human Spermatozoa Morphology</span></h2>
<p>A: Normal spermatozoa observed at high magnification (≥ 8400×, in original figure)
</p><p>A spermatozoon was classified as morphologically normal when it exhibited a normal nucleus (smooth, symmetric and oval nucleus, width 3.28 +/- 0.20 micron, length 4.75 +/- 0.20 micron/absence of vacuoles occupying &gt; 4% of nuclear area) as well as acrosome, post-acrosomal lamina, neck and tail, besides not presenting cytoplasm around the head. 
</p><p><br />
</p>
<dl><dd><a href="/embryology/index.php?title=Spermatozoa_Development" title="Spermatozoa Development"><b>Spermatozoa Images</b></a>: <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=File:Human-spermatozoa.jpg" title="File:Human-spermatozoa.jpg">Spermatozoa BF</a> | <a class="mw-selflink selflink">Spermatozoon BF</a> | <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=File:Human-spermatozoa_EM01.jpg" title="File:Human-spermatozoa EM01.jpg">Spermatozoon EM</a> | <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=File:Human_spermatid_electron_micrograph.jpg" title="File:Human spermatid electron micrograph.jpg">Spermatozoon EM</a> | <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=File:Bailey008.jpg" title="File:Bailey008.jpg">Historic drawing</a> | <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=Category:Spermatozoa" title="Category:Spermatozoa">Category:Spermatozoa</a> | <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=Spermatozoa_Development" title="Spermatozoa Development">Spermatozoa Development</a> | <a href="/embryology/index.php?title=Testis_Development" title="Testis Development">Testis Development</a></dd></dl>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Reference">Reference</span></h3>
<p>&lt;pubmed&gt;20529256&lt;/pubmed&gt;| <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.rbej.com/content/8/1/56">Reprod Biol Endocrinol.</a>
</p>
